5.3 Full Hand Grasp Simulation
In order to truly simulate the grasps, full knowledge of the system would be necessary, including mass distribution, compliance and orientation with respect to gravity. As such, the simulations are run without any interactions between the object and the hand. Thresholding the errors at 1 degree, 11 of the 32 grasps are accomplished with 0 error in any of the joints. 4 of the remaining grasps demonstrate no error in any of the

fingers which contact the object. The error free grasps consist of the following: Allen Wrench, Alligator Clip, BNC Cable, Eraser, Floppy Disk, Open Pliers, Button, Open and Closed Scissors, Screwdriver, and White Out. The four contact-error free grasps consist of the following: Thumbtack, Pencil, Tweezers, and Battery. Shown below are the grasps which demonstrate some level of error, with the desired configuration on the right and the simulated configuration on the left.

